House Resolution 382
By: Representatives Sanchez of the 42nd, McQueen of the 61st, and Alexander of the 66th
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and commending Cobb Collaborative, recipient of the Georgia Reads
2 Community Award, for its dedication to literacy advancement; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Council on Literacy is dedicated to improving literacy from birth
4 through adulthood and recognizes that communities play a critical role in addressing low
5 literacy rates; and
6 WHEREAS, the Georgia Reads Community Award was established to recognize
7 communities across Georgia that have formed partnerships of two or more organizations,
8 sustained for at least three years, with a strategic plan and measurable results in literacy
9 improvement; and
10 WHEREAS, Cobb Collaborative serves as the local point of contact for the Get Georgia
11 Reading Campaign, engaging a cross-sector group of child and family-facing advocates to
12 support community-wide literacy strategies; and
13 WHEREAS, Cobb Collaborative has fostered meaningful partnerships with Cobb County
14 Public Library, Cobb Douglas Public Health, First Christian Church of Mableton, Marietta
15 City Schools, faith communities, the Georgia Department of Early Care and Learning, other
