16 nonprofit organizations, and Smyrna Library to expand access to literacy resources and
17 educational support; and
18 WHEREAS, these initiatives have led to measurable improvements in reading proficiency,
19 creating greater opportunities for academic success and career development; and
20 WHEREAS, the dedication and hard work of Cobb Collaborative and its partners serve as
21 an inspiration to others, demonstrating the power of community-driven solutions to address
22 literacy challenges.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body congratulate and commend the Georgia Reads Community Award
25 recipients, particularly Cobb Collaborative, for their exemplary service and unwavering
26 commitment to improving literacy in their communities.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Cobb
29 Collaborative.
